Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain and pop back in the pan. Cover and set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g}, @Mangetout{80%g} and @Sliced Mushrooms{80%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a #bowl{}, combine the @Sweet Chilli Sauce{48%g}, @Peanut Butter{30%g}, @Soy Sauce{25%ml} and @Boiled Water{100%ml}.

Add the @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and sauce to the pan.

Simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a splash of water if it's looking a little thick.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the beef stir-fry.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g}.

Enjoy!